1
00:00:04,735 --> 00:00:07,425
You have to reconceive light.

2
00:00:09,041 --> 00:00:13,634
When we think, ‘jyoti’—
in this way it’s connected—

3
00:00:14,409 --> 00:00:17,037
‘jyoti’, 
we think, ‘illumination’.

4
00:00:17,037 --> 00:00:22,818
We know, to become enlightened,
illumined,

5
00:00:23,049 --> 00:00:25,673
that’s another type of luminosity;

6
00:00:25,673 --> 00:00:28,078
[Air Bhajan]

7
00:00:28,864 --> 00:00:33,839
light, illumination,
is revelation.

8
00:00:34,274 --> 00:00:38,620
So what is light
in the conscious plane?

9
00:00:38,620 --> 00:00:42,700
I’m not talking about 
objective light—

10
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:48,339
we see the sunrise,
how beautiful it is, and it is,

11
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:53,546
it’s been compared to 
the lotus eyes of Viṣṇu—

12
00:00:55,215 --> 00:00:59,460
but Guru Mahārāj, 
in his gāyatrī explanation,

13
00:00:59,460 --> 00:01:03,509
oṁ bhūr bhuvaḥ svah tat savitur
varenyaṁ bhargo,

14
00:01:07,558 --> 00:01:11,607
is saying that this superficially 
appears to be talking about the sun:

15
00:01:13,472 --> 00:01:16,523
how the sun
is illuminating the world;

16
00:01:16,523 --> 00:01:19,000
the sun reveals the world.

17
00:01:19,230 --> 00:01:23,859
When we’re, especially,
in the Kṛṣṇa-pakṣa

18
00:01:23,859 --> 00:01:30,826
—means the dark moon; 
no visible moon—

19
00:01:30,994 --> 00:01:34,849
we wait for the sunrise 
to reveal everything,

20
00:01:35,503 --> 00:01:37,530
but he’s saying, 
bhūr bhuvaḥ svah:

21
00:01:37,530 --> 00:01:39,173
the whole world of experience

22
00:01:39,173 --> 00:01:41,629
—the lower, middle, 
higher, planetary systems—

23
00:01:41,629 --> 00:01:46,929
means the world of experience,
the objective world;

24
00:01:46,929 --> 00:01:50,958
it appears on one level
to be revealed by the sun,

25
00:01:50,958 --> 00:02:01,396
but actually it’s ātmā, the soul, 
that reveals everything.

26
00:02:02,241 --> 00:02:08,931
Without the conscious observer,
it’s meaningless.

27
00:02:08,931 --> 00:02:14,811
So really it’s a position 
occupied by the soul, ātmā,

28
00:02:14,811 --> 00:02:18,846
and by extension, Paramātmā.

29
00:02:20,437 --> 00:02:26,063
So there is the Paramātmā domain,
world,

30
00:02:26,063 --> 00:02:30,351
that is vareṇyam, worshipable.

31
00:02:30,351 --> 00:02:34,886
And here—
bhargo vai vṛsabhānujātma-vibhavai—

32
00:02:36,603 --> 00:02:40,317
Guru Mahārāj is saying,

33
00:02:40,317 --> 00:02:46,245
“And the halo of 
Śrīmati Rādhārāṇī is faith,

34
00:02:46,245 --> 00:02:51,018
and that which reveals Kṛṣṇa 
and Kṛṣṇa conception.”

35
00:02:51,018 --> 00:02:55,134
We were talking about 
Her bhāva and kānti,

36
00:02:55,134 --> 00:02:57,259
Her heart and halo;

37
00:02:57,259 --> 00:03:03,151
the halo is the outcome
of Her heart,

38
00:03:03,151 --> 00:03:06,162
so it’s the heart 
of Śrīmati Rādhārāṇī

39
00:03:06,162 --> 00:03:09,846
that is actually illuminating 
Kṛṣṇa conception

40
00:03:09,846 --> 00:03:13,177
and the service of Kṛṣṇa,

41
00:03:14,251 --> 00:03:16,044
and without that,

42
00:03:16,044 --> 00:03:24,289
it’s all imagination, fictitious, wallpaper,
air bhajan.

